Active Directory Domain Services (AD DS) – Full Procedure
PART 1: Install Active Directory Domain Services
Step 1: Open Server Manager

Login to Windows Server

Open Server Manager

Step 2: Add Roles and Features

Click Manage

Select Add Roles and Features

Click Next

Select Role-based or feature-based installation

Click Next

Select Local Server

Click Next

Step 3: Select Server Role

Select Active Directory Domain Services

Click Add Features

Click Next

Click Next

Click Install

Step 4: Promote Server to Domain Controller

After installation, click Promote this server to a domain controller

Select Add a new forest

Enter Domain Name
Example: company.local

Click Next

Step 5: Domain Controller Options

Select:

Forest Functional Level: Windows Server 2016 or above

Domain Functional Level: Windows Server 2016 or above

Set DSRM Password

Click Next

Step 6: DNS Configuration

Click Next

Ignore DNS delegation warning

Step 7: NetBIOS Name

NetBIOS name will auto-fill (Example: COMPANY)

Click Next

Step 8: Paths

Leave default paths

Click Next

Click Install

Step 9: Restart

Server will restart automatically

Login using:

COMPANY\Administrator

PART 2: Create Active Directory User
Step 1: Open Active Directory Users and Computers

Open Server Manager

Click Tools

Select Active Directory Users and Computers

Step 2: Create Organizational Unit (Optional)

Right-click domain name

Click New → Organizational Unit

Enter Name
Example: IT_Users

Click OK

Step 3: Create New User

Right-click OU or Users

Select New → User

Enter:

First Name: Sachin

User logon name: sachin

Click Next

Step 4: Set Password

Enter Password

Uncheck User must change password at next logon (optional)

Check Password never expires (optional)

Click Next

Click Finish

PART 3: Join Another Machine to Domain (Client Machine)
Requirement

Windows 10 / Windows 11

Network connectivity between Server and Client

DNS of client must point to Domain Controller IP

Step 1: Set DNS on Client Machine

Open Network Settings

Open Adapter Properties

Select IPv4

Set Preferred DNS Server as Domain Controller IP
Example:

DNS: 192.168.1.10

Step 2: Join Domain

Open This PC

Right-click → Properties

Click Advanced system settings

Click Computer Name

Click Change

Select Domain

Enter Domain Name
Example:

company.local


Click OK

Step 3: Provide Domain Credentials

Enter:

Username: Administrator
Password: Domain password


Click OK

Restart Client Machine

PART 4: Login with Domain User from Another Machine
Step 1: Login Screen

After restart, select Other user

Step 2: Enter Domain User Credentials

Username:

company\sachin


or

sachin@company.local


Enter Password

Click Sign in

Verification

User profile will be created

Domain login successful

Client machine is now part of the domain

Conclusion

Active Directory is successfully installed.
User account is created and login is verified from another machine.
